title: Gustafsson, Warren reach doubles main draw
text:
Gustafsson, Warren reach doubles main draw From our community Houston Community Newspapers 
Adam Gustasson and David Warren advanced to the main draw of the men’s doubles with a pair of wins while teammates Jamie Malik and Tommy Bennett upset the 40th ranked doubles team in the country to highlight second-day action at the 2015 Saint Francis Health System ITA Men's All-American Championships in Tulsa, Oklahoma. 
Gustafsson and Warren opened play on Wednesday morning by posting their own upset, grinding out a tiebreak win over Wichita State’s 42nd ranked Jocelyn Devilliers and Tin Ostojic, 6-2, 3-6, 1-0(8). They came back in the afternoon to take down North Carolina’s Jack Murray and Ronnie Schneider, 7-6(5), 6-4 to advance to the main draw. Advertisement 
The Owls’ duo will face off LSU’s Boris Arias and Jordan Daigle, who were ranked third in the fall rankings, at 2 p.m. at the Michael D. Case Tennis Center on the campus of the University of Tulsa. 
Bennett and Malik gave the Owls a pair of victories over top 50 doubles teams when they raced to a 6-2, 6-4 win over No. 40 Dominic Cotrone and Sasha Gozun of South Florida. The fell short of their goal of joining their teammates in the main draw when the dropped a 7-5, 6-0 decision to Wake Forest’s Jonathan Ho-Keivon Tabrizi.
